About

massdatabase is a R package which is used for metabolite identification based on in-house database and public database based on accurate mass (m/z), retention time (RT) and/or MS2 spectra.

Installation

You can install massdatabase from GitLab

if(!require(remotes)){
install.packages("remotes")
}
remotes::install_gitlab("jaspershen/massdatabase")

or Github

remotes::install_github("tidymass/massdatabase")

massdatabase is a part of tidymass, so you can also install it by installing tidymass.

Usage

Please see the Help documents page to get the instruction of massdatabase.
